      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET TREATS (8) slow into stride when she motored late from near last on the turn with a slashing fifth over 1400m at Wagga. Saves her best for this track and trip and can put these away. PHILADELPHIA STORM (1) resumed from a lengthy break with a courageous second over 1600m at Albury shouldering the 61.5kg. Back in good order and capable of going one better. STAR BLAZER (3) failed to keep in touch first-up with a battling tenth over 1300m at Echuca. Comes to hand quickly and gets to his pet trip with the claim. Each way. WALK THE PIER (6) set to peak with the winkers going on fourth-up. Snagged back from the wide gate and never got into the contest with a poor tenth over 1500m at Hawkesbury. Gets a better set-up for this and has solid prospects.",
